<h2>Filtering</h2>

<h3>filter</h3>

<div class="param">
  <p class="param__bit param__bit--type">
    <span class="param__bit__title">Type:</span>
    <span class="param__bit__value"><i>String</i> or <i>Function</i></span>
  </p>
</div>

<p>Shows items that match the filter and hides items that do not match. See <a href="filtering.html">docs on Filtering</a>.</p>

<p>If set to a string, that value is used as a <a href="filtering.html#selectors">selector</a>.</p>

``` js
$container.isotope({ filter: '.selector' });
```

<p>If <a href="filtering.html#functions"><code>filter</code> is set to a function</a>, that function checks each item and returns <code>true</code> or <code>false</code> if the item should be shown or hidden.</p>

``` js
$container.isotope({
  // filter element with numbers greater than 50
  filter: function() {
    // _this_ is the item element. Get text of element's .number
    var number = $(this).find('.number').text();
    // return true to show, false to hide
    return parseInt( number, 10 ) > 50;
  }
});
```

